The paper deals with graphical models and decision making, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of graphical models to represent conditional independences also suggests a possible fit with the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper also discusses the construction of a directed expected utility network to support decision making, which could be relevant to the social and information sciences (cs.SI) and computational engineering (cs.CE) categories.
